headlines.description: Chelsea cemented their place in the Premier League's top four and dealt another major blow to Leeds' survival hopes with a 2-0 win at Elland Road.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pulisic on target as Leeds suffer survival blow

headlines.shortLinkText: Leicester's Rodgers says 'every minute counts' for veteran Var

headlines.description: Relegated Watford ended a run of 11 straight home defeats when they held Everton to a goalless draw in a poor Premier League encounter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Everton earn point in drab draw with Watford

headlines.description: Kevin De Bruyne scored a first-half hat trick as Manchester City rolled past Wolves 5-1 at Molineux on Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: De Bruyne nets 4 as Man City restore PL lead
